This is a Roblox game project with the following structure:

## Core Directories

- [src/](mdc:src) - Contains all game code
  - [src/ReplicatedStorage/](mdc:src/ReplicatedStorage) - Shared code between server and client
    - [src/ReplicatedStorage/Systems/](mdc:src/ReplicatedStorage/Systems) - Game systems that follow the system architecture
    - [src/ReplicatedStorage/modules/](mdc:src/ReplicatedStorage/modules) - Utility modules and libraries
    - [src/ReplicatedStorage/configs/](mdc:src/ReplicatedStorage/configs) - Configuration files and constants
   - System assets are colocated per system under `src/ReplicatedStorage/Systems/<SystemName>/Assets/` (e.g., `GrassSystem/Assets`, `WeaponSystem/Assets`)
  - [src/ServerScriptService/](mdc:src/ServerScriptService) - Server-only scripts and entry points
    - Contains server initialization scripts
    - Server-specific logic that doesn't fit into the systems architecture
  - [src/StarterGui/](mdc:src/StarterGui) - User interface elements loaded when player joins
    - [src/StarterGui/Main/](mdc:src/StarterGui/Main) - Main UI components
    - [uiController.lua](mdc:src/StarterGui/Main/uiController.lua) - Centralized UI interaction management
    - UI controllers and local scripts
  - [src/StarterPlayer/](mdc:src/StarterPlayer) - Player scripts and settings
    - [src/StarterPlayer/StarterPlayerScripts/](mdc:src/StarterPlayer/StarterPlayerScripts) - Scripts that run for each player
    - [src/StarterPlayer/StarterCharacterScripts/](mdc:src/StarterPlayer/StarterCharacterScripts) - Scripts that run on the player's character
  - [src/ServerStorage/](mdc:src/ServerStorage) - Server-only storage for classes and data
    - [src/ServerStorage/classes/](mdc:src/ServerStorage/classes) - Server-side classes
  - [src/ReplicatedFirst/](mdc:src/ReplicatedFirst) - Code that loads immediately when player joins
    - Loading screen and initial setup

## Configuration Files

- [wally.toml](mdc:wally.toml) - Dependency management for Roblox packages
- [default.project.json](mdc:default.project.json) - Roblox Studio project configuration
- [aftman.toml](mdc:aftman.toml) - Tool manager configuration
- [selene.toml](mdc:selene.toml) - Lua linter configuration
- [Packages/](mdc:Packages) - Installed third-party packages (Wally)

## Adding New Files

When adding new files to the project:

1. Place files in the appropriate directory based on their purpose
2. Follow the established naming conventions from the coding standards
3. For systems, use the Template system as a starting point
4. For UI components, follow the structure in StarterGui
5. For server-side classes, add to the ServerStorage/classes directory
6. Place assets under the relevant system's `Assets/` folder
